es.sh inside your project and to \"source\" it.\n\nBut, if you want to make it available for the entire system, or for local\nuser, you can use the make install command:\n\n    \n    \n    # install inside the system # in /usr/local/lib sudo make install # for local user, no need to use sudo, but change the PREFIX make install PREFIX=~/.local/lib\n\nYou can then uninstall the library file:\n\n    \n    \n    sudo make uninstall make uninstall PREFIX=~/.loca/bin\n\n## License\n\n## About\n\nA simple curses library made in bash to draw terminal interfaces\n\n### Topics\n\nbash terminal curses\n\n### Resources\n\nReadme\n\n### License\n\nBSD-3-Clause license\n\nActivity\n\n### Stars\n\n691 stars\n\n### Watchers\n\n22 watching\n\n### Forks\n\n112 forks\n\nReport repository\n\n## Releases 4\n\n1.3 version Latest\n\nFeb 12, 2019\n\n\\+ 3 releases\n\n## Packages 0\n\nNo packages published\n\n## Contributors 17\n\n\\+ 3 contributors\n\n## Languages\n\n  * Shell 92.3%\n  * Makefile 7.7%\n\n## Footer\n\n\u00a9 2024 GitHub, Inc.\n\nYou can\u2019t perform that action at this time.\n\n", "frontpage": false}
